How to get the Sid of a windows machine using netstandard classes.In .NET Framework we have ManagementObject class and using win32 query we can get the sid or using the following code we can get the sid 
var user = WindowsIdentity.GetCurrent().User;
        string sid = UserPrincipal.Current.Sid.ToString();

How to get sid using netstandard classes. Neither UserPrincipal nor ManagementObject classes are present in netstandard classes

When following the [ObjectWriter build doc](https://github.com/dotnet/corert/blob/master/Documentation/how-to-build-ObjectWriter.md) I encountered an issue wherein various members of the `ICorDebugInfo` class in [ObjWriter/cordebuginfo.h](https://github.com/dotnet/corert/blob/master/src/Native/ObjWriter/objwriter.cpp) triggered an error due to [class scope](http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2012/n3337.pdf#subsection.3.3.7) issues. Specifically redefining a few structs without using elaborated type specifiers in the `VarLoc` struct.  

```
    struct VarLoc
    {
        VarLocType      vlType;

        union
        {
            vlReg           vlReg;
            vlStk           vlStk;
            vlRegReg        vlRegReg;
            vlRegStk        vlRegStk;
            vlStkReg        vlStkReg;
            vlStk2          vlStk2;
            vlFPstk         vlFPstk;
            vlFixedVarArg   vlFixedVarArg;
            vlMemory        vlMemory;
        };
};
```

